title: TOWIE's James Lock cannot stop smiling as he shoots scenes | Daily Mail Online
text: Share this article Share Yazmin was determined to look sensational for her screen debut as she wore an incredibly plunging black top which flashed her bust. In an attempt to shun the chill, she wore a sleeveless waistcoat with a charcoal colour and a thick belt to nip in her tiny waist. Moving on: The 30-year-old hunk went for a low-key ensemble as he pulled on a bomber jacket and flat cap while his stunning companion opted for a similar colour scheme while flaunting her eye-popping cleavage Flaunting all her best assets, she also wore skin-tight jeans while tucking the trousers into a pair of thigh-high boots. Proving she will slot perfectly into the Essex girl ethos, she wore extremely heavy make-up paired with a mahogany tan. Her raven tresses were styled into bouncy waves falling over her shoulders while tumbling from a centre parting. While James seems to have found new love, Danielle has moved on after confirming her relationship with former footballer Daniel Spiller in December. Over: Last year, his relationship with Danielle Armstrong came to a devastating end New love: While James seems to have found new love, Danielle has moved on after confirming her relationship with former footballer Daniel Spiller in December And a recent Instagram post suggests the former star has already worked her magic on her latest boyfriend. Taking to the social media platform, Daniel – an ex Millwall and Gillingham midfielder – shared a snap of himself seated alongside the voluptuous TV personality, whose cleavage is evident beneath the plunging neckline of her black dress. Referring to Instagram’s popular ‘Woman Crush Wednesday’ hashtag, he wrote: ‘I guess my #wcw goes out to this weapon.’ Busty babe: Taking to the social media platform, Daniel – an ex Millwall and Gillingham midfielder – shared a snap of himself seated alongside the voluptuous TV personality, whose cleavage is evident beneath the plunging neckline of her black dress Sources previously told The Sun that Danielle, who joined the cast of TOWIE in 2013 as James Lock's girlfriend, is distancing herself from her ex-beau as she delightedly dates Daniel - who she is said to be 'really keen' on. The Maidstone-born footballer, who has most recently been playing for non-league Herne Bay in the Ryman League Division One South, made more than 150 appearances for Gillingham over two periods. Daniel, who was known as ‘Spills’, became a favourite among Gills fans who used to sing the chant ‘Spills will tear you apart again’ to the tune of Love Will Tear Us Apart by Joy Division.
